<div class="tip_number">TIP 150</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            In rare cases, a darkening and thickening of the skin around the back of the neck, armpits, and groin of an adult (usually over forty years of age) can be the sign of a serious disease, including certain cancers and/or diabetes.
        </div>

